From: Alexander Stein <alexander.stein@ew.tq-group.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Apr 2024 13:36:29 +0200
Subject: i2c: lpi2c: Avoid calling clk_get_rate during transfer
Git-commit: 4268254a39484fc11ba991ae148bacbe75d9cc0a
Patch-mainline: v6.10
References: bsc#1227885 CVE-2024-40965

Instead of repeatedly calling clk_get_rate for each transfer, lock
the clock rate and cache the value.
A deadlock has been observed while adding tlv320aic32x4 audio codec to
the system. When this clock provider adds its clock, the clk mutex is
locked already, it needs to access i2c, which in return needs the mutex
for clk_get_rate as well.

Backporting notes:
* The API to lock the clock rate (clk_rate_exclusive_get) was not
  available yet, so we just hope that nobody else will attempt
  to change the clock rate behind our back.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Stein <alexander.stein@ew.tq-group.com>
Reviewed-by: Uwe Kleine-König <u.kleine-koenig@pengutronix.de>
Reviewed-by: Andi Shyti <andi.shyti@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Andi Shyti <andi.shyti@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Jean Delvare <jdelvare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-imx-lpi2c.c |   14 +++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-imx-lpi2c.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-imx-lpi2c.c
@@ -112,6 +112,7 @@ struct lpi2c_imx_struct {
 	__u8			*rx_buf;
 	__u8			*tx_buf;
 	struct completion	complete;
+	unsigned long		rate_per;
 	unsigned int		msglen;
 	unsigned int		delivered;
 	unsigned int		block_data;
@@ -222,7 +223,7 @@ static int lpi2c_imx_config(struct lpi2c
 
 	lpi2c_imx_set_mode(lpi2c_imx);
 
-	clk_rate = clk_get_rate(lpi2c_imx->clk);
+	clk_rate = lpi2c_imx->rate_per;
 	if (lpi2c_imx->mode == HS || lpi2c_imx->mode == ULTRA_FAST)
 		filt = 0;
 	else
@@ -606,6 +607,17 @@ static int lpi2c_imx_probe(struct platfo
 		return ret;
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * Ideally we would lock the clock rate, unfortunately the API
+	 * to do this isn't available yet
+	 */
+	lpi2c_imx->rate_per = clk_get_rate(lpi2c_imx->clk);
+	if (!lpi2c_imx->rate_per) {
+		dev_err(&pdev->dev, "can't get I2C peripheral clock rate\n");
+		ret = -EINVAL;
+		goto clk_unprepare;
+	}
+
 	temp = readl(lpi2c_imx->base + LPI2C_PARAM);
 	lpi2c_imx->txfifosize = 1 << (temp & 0x0f);
 	lpi2c_imx->rxfifosize = 1 << ((temp >> 8) & 0x0f);
